Stephanie Izard 

  ·   ·
After a fun week of cooking, Tine Gill's suggestion inspired me to pick up some sockeye salmon and veggies and make a fun filled platter of tasty!
My new Instant Pot Omni cooks the salmon so perfectly and turns my fav Hawaiian mission tortillas in to crunchy tostadas. Chili lime crunch mayo can make anything delish! And summery tomato, avocado and corn to top it all off!
So summery. Light. Bright. Full of flavor. And quick & easy!
Just right Please keep sending along summertime inspo!
Salmon:
  • Marinate lime juice, salt, and oil from This Little Goat chili lime crunch
  • Air fry 450 degrees for about 7 min
Mission Tortillas:
  • Olive oil and salt
  • Air fry 450 for 4-5 min until puffed and golden
Tomato salad:
  • Roasted corn, cilantro, salt, chili lime crunch
  • Sliced Red onions, jalepeno, lime juice, salt and pinch sugar
  • Kewpie mayo + chili lime crunch + lime juice
  • Also: radish, avocado, more cilantro, queso fresco
